<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1455,1661]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1492,1518]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Remarks.</emphasis>
Only the sexual generation has been described. The alternating lifecycle was closed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Tang, C. - T. &amp; Sinclair, F. &amp; Hearn, J. &amp; Yang M. - M. &amp; Stone, G. N. &amp; Nicholls J. A. &amp; Schweger, S. &amp; Melika, G." pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="451 - 488" refId="ref53913" refString="Tang, C. - T., Sinclair, F., Hearn, J., Yang M. - M., Stone, G. N., Nicholls J. A., Schweger, S. &amp; Melika, G. (2016 b) Eight new species of Cycloneuroterus Melika &amp; Tang gallwasps from Taiwan and mainland China (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Cynipini). Zootaxa, 4088 (4), 451 - 488. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4088.4.1" type="journal article" year="2016">
Tang 
<emphasis box="[1379,1429,1491,1517]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al</emphasis>
. (2016b)
</bibRefCitation>
on the basis of DNA sequences obtained from larvae dissected from asexual generation galls.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1455,1661]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1563,1589]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Biology.</emphasis>
The sexual generation induces integral galls on very young leaves of 
<taxonomicName authority="Blume" authorityName="Blume" box="[1082,1318,1563,1590]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sessilifolia">
<emphasis box="[1082,1236,1563,1590]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Q. sessilifolia</emphasis>
Blume
</taxonomicName>
, while the asexual generation induces detachable leaf galls on 
<taxonomicName box="[730,820,1599,1626]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gilva">
<emphasis box="[730,820,1599,1626]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Q. gilva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(both in section 
<taxonomicName box="[1008,1195,1599,1625]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Cyclobalanopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1008,1195,1599,1625]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Cyclobalanopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (Table 1; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tang, C. - T. &amp; Sinclair, F. &amp; Hearn, J. &amp; Yang M. - M. &amp; Stone, G. N. &amp; Nicholls J. A. &amp; Schweger, S. &amp; Melika, G." pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="451 - 488" refId="ref53913" refString="Tang, C. - T., Sinclair, F., Hearn, J., Yang M. - M., Stone, G. N., Nicholls J. A., Schweger, S. &amp; Melika, G. (2016 b) Eight new species of Cycloneuroterus Melika &amp; Tang gallwasps from Taiwan and mainland China (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Cynipini). Zootaxa, 4088 (4), 451 - 488. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4088.4.1" type="journal article" year="2016">
Tang 
<emphasis box="[1380,1429,1599,1625]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al</emphasis>
. 2016b
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
